algorithms

Interface SchedulingAlgorithm

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSchedulingAlgorithm, FirstComeFirstServe, NonPreemptiveAlgorithm

    public interface SchedulingAlgorithm
    Scheduling Algorithm Interface. This is to implement the flow input -> process -> output / | \ / | \ jobs algorithm (a) Gantt Chart (b) Results This is the interface to be used by the end-programmers.

    • Method Detail

      • processJobs

        AlgorithmResult processJobs(Job[] jobs)
        Processes a set of jobs. This method provides its own copy of the jobs, therefore it is safe to reuse the Job array passed into this method to another Scheduling Algorithm.
        Parameters:
        jobs - The array of jobs
        Returns:
        The algorithm result
